

# Jank SDL example #

Simple example of how to use SDL with Jank.


Heavily based on [Beginning Game Programming v2.0](https://lazyfoo.net/tutorials/SDL/).


On Ubuntu, you can run it with a simple `lein run`. On other platforms, you
might have to adjust the include paths. This requirement will likely go away in
upcoming versions of Jank, unless you wan to use a nonstandard location for your
SDL library.

